  "clinical_criteria": [
    "Age 50 or older at time of earliest inclusion surgery OR initial inclusion diagnosis for CASES",
    "Age 50 or older at time of most recent optical exam for CONTROLS",
    "Subjects less than 50 years of age at time of earliest surgery OR earliest inclusion diagnosis date are EXCLUDED",
    "Subjects less than 50 years of age at the most recent optical exam are EXCLUDED",
    "At least 1 cataract surgery procedure from CPT codes specified",
    "1 or more eye exam(s) in the past 5 years from current date (<=1826 days)",
    "Exclude traumatic, congenital and juvenile cataract surgery codes",
    "Exclude reversed and reversal records, include only production records",
    "Provider must be a clinical provider",
    "Use diagnoses from 1960 to present",
    "Exclude non-clinical providers for diagnoses",
    "Exclude diagnoses: Congenital Cataract (743.30-743.34), Traumatic Cataract (366.20-366.23), Juvenile Cataract (366.00-366.09, 366.11), After Cataract (366.50-366.53)",
    "Include diagnoses: Senile Cataract (366.10-366.19, 366.21, 366.30, 366.41, 366.45, 366.8), Unspecified Cataract (366.9)",
    "NLP certainty exclusions: cannot evaluate, ignore, insignificant, low, low certainty, none, negative, possible other findings, rule out, very low, very low certainty, scheduled",
    "Long-term adrenal steroid use determined by 2 or more unique diagnosis dates for specified conditions plus steroid medication mentions",
    "ICR and NLP used to identify cataract subtypes: nuclear sclerotic, posterior subcapsular, cortical"
  ],
  "algorithm_summary": "This algorithm identifies cataract cases and controls from the Personalized Medicine Research Project cohort. Cases are defined as subjects aged \u226550 years with at least one cataract surgery (CPT codes 66982-66986, 66830-66940) or qualifying inclusion ICD-9 diagnoses (366.10-366.9 range, excluding traumatic, congenital, juvenile, and after-cataract types 366.00-366.11, 366.20-366.23, 366.50-366.53, 743.30-743.34). Controls are subjects aged \u226550 who had an eye exam (CPT 92002-92019) within the past 5 years but no cataract diagnosis. The algorithm employs Natural Language Processing (MedLEE with UMLS CUIs) and Intelligent Character Recognition to identify cataract subtypes (nuclear sclerotic, posterior subcapsular, cortical) and laterality from clinical notes and ophthalmology forms. Additional analysis captures long-term adrenal steroid use as a risk factor, identified through diagnosis codes for conditions like COPD, Crohn's disease, rheumatoid arthritis, lupus, transplant status, and specific steroid medication mentions (prednisone, dexamethasone, methylprednisolone, etc.).",
  "analysis_timestamp": "2026-05-02T20:06:39.264857Z"
